# Ory Hydra v26.2.0 — SQLite-enabled binary (CGO build with libsqlite3).
# File: hydra_26.2.0-linux_sqlite_64bit.tar.gz
# Source: https://github.com/ory/hydra/releases/tag/v26.2.0
# Verified: 2026-04-21
#
# WHY THE SQLITE VARIANT (not the default linux_64bit build):
# Ory ships two Linux amd64 tarballs per release — the default is
# compiled WITHOUT SQLite support (MySQL/Postgres/CockroachDB only).
# A SQLite-flavoured CGO build lives behind the `-sqlite_64bit` suffix.
# Our DSN is sqlite:///var/lib/jabali-hydra/db.sqlite3 (ADR-0036
# amendment), so the default binary errors out at migrate time with
# "SQLite support was not built into the binary. Binary archives
# indicate SQLite support by appending the -sqlite suffix".
#
# Ory switched Hydra from semver (v2.3.0 was the last) to calendar
# versioning starting with v25.4.0. v26.2.0 (March 2026) is the latest
# stable. Prior pin was v2.3.0 (Jan 2024) — 2+ years of upstream
# patches, including the "Down migrations in newer MySQL versions"
# fix called out in release notes.
28baf98c6d5da617c905d5ca77826fe863db9f9edab8f72664c69a56bde56b5a  hydra_26.2.0-linux_sqlite_64bit.tar.gz
